 opportunities offered by <span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">ASIAN AMERICAN GOVERNMENT EXECUTIVES NETWORK. Application deadline is 4/30. Please see the attachment for details.</span> </span></span></div>\r\n<div>3. The Council of Asian and Pacific Americans in Michign is sponsoring an Asian Cultural Dance Performance Show \"Splendor of the East\" on Friday, May 14, 2010 at 7 p.m. at Ford Community\r\nand Performing Arts Center in Dearborn. The organizer is looking for 2-3 volunteers from Chinese organization for the following work on May14:</div>\r\n<div>* food set up for the VIP reception</div>\r\n<div>* usher guests into the auditorium</div>\r\n<div>* runners for program participants</div>\r\n<div>* Others</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span>There will be discount in admission </span><span>( or possible free admission) for volunteers. </span>This is a good opoortunity to let youngsters to participate in this international cultural event. Please contact \"Sue Sung\" [<a href=\"mailto:sue.sung@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">sue.sung@gmail.com</a>] if you are interested. The poster is too big to send, you may find more details from the website <a title=\"http://capa-mi.org/\" href=\"http://capa-mi.org/\" target=\"_blank\">capa-mi.org</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>4.  Big Coming Event that I encourage all families to participate:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n\r\n<strong>*</strong><strong>Taiwanese American Heritage Week Cultural Fair*</strong>\r\n<strong>\r\nFriday</strong>, May 7th, 6:30-8pm @ Duderstadt Center Connector, The University of Michigan North Campus, 2281 Bonisteel Boulevard, Ann Arbor\r\n<strong>Saturday</strong>, May 8th, 10am-3pm @ Sheraton Hotel, 21111 Haggerty Road, Novi.\r\n\r\nIn celebration of Taiwanese American Heritage Week, all are invited to join the unique opportunity to see cultural presentations by renowned Taiwanese folk artisans in:\r\n* Lion Head (used in Lion Dance) Painting\r\n* Hand Puppetry\r\n* Dough Figuring Sculpture\r\n* Sugar Sculpture\r\n* Gourd Carving\r\n* Paper Umbrella Painting\r\n* Sculpture using tree bark, leaves, and other natural materials..\r\n* Silhouette paper cutting\r\nHands-on activities available for children and adults.   For details and  directions, please visit <a title=\"http://www.mitai.org\" href=\"http://www.mitai.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.mitai.org</a>.\r\n\r\nFREE. Donations welcome to help cover the material fees.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\r\n\r\nHave a great week!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Best Regards</div>\r\n<div>Alex Tang</div>\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/final_with_three_essays_and_one_time_change1.doc\">final_with_three_essays_and_one_time_change[1]</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/tennis.doc\">tennis</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Novi-poster1.jpg\">Novi poster.jpg</a>','MCS Communication - 4/17/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-4172010','','','2010-04-16 23:00:34','2010-04-17 03:00:34','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=58',0,'post','',0),(59,1,'2010-04-16 22:50:47','2010-04-17 02:50:47','','Novi poster',0,'','inherit','open','open','','novi-poster','','','2010-04-16 22:50:47','2010-04-17 02:50:47','',58,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Novi-poster.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(60,1,'2010-04-16 22:51:44','2010-04-17 02:51:44','','Novi poster',0,'','inherit','open','open','','novi-poster-2','','','2010-04-16 22:51:44','2010-04-17 02:51:44','',58,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Novi-poster1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(61,1,'2010-04-16 22:53:48','2010-04-17 02:53:48','','tennis',0,'','inherit','open